<section class="program-content">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="program-content__grid">
      <div class="program-content__main">
        <div class="program-content__section">
          <h2 class="program-content__heading font-display">What It Is</h2>
          <p>FLOOR is AHG&rsquo;s flagship fellowship. It places 8&ndash;12 exceptional young leaders inside legislative offices, policy organizations, and reform-focused institutions where laws are written and power is exercised.</p>
          <p>Fellows do not observe. They draft policy language, analyze legislation, build stakeholder coalitions, and produce a capstone reform proposal that targets a real issue in Texas law or local ordinance.</p>
          <p>This is the most competitive program AHG offers. Selection is rigorous. The work is harder.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="program-content__section">
          <h2 class="program-content__heading font-display">Selection</h2>
          <p>Each cohort accepts 8&ndash;12 fellows from a competitive applicant pool. We look for demonstrated commitment to reform, clear analytical thinking, and the ability to hold your ground in rooms that were not built for you.</p>
          <p>Prior policy experience is not required. Conviction is.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

