<section class="program-phases">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="program-phases__title font-display">The Fellowship</h2>
    <div class="program-phases__timeline">

      <div class="program-phase">
        <span class="program-phase__number font-mono">01</span>
        <div class="program-phase__content">
          <h3 class="program-phase__name font-display">Placement</h3>
          <p>Fellows are matched with legislative offices, policy organizations, or reform institutions based on their issue focus and strengths.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="program-phase">
        <span class="program-phase__number font-mono">02</span>
        <div class="program-phase__content">
          <h3 class="program-phase__name font-display">Policy Curriculum</h3>
          <p>A structured curriculum in legislative analysis, policy writing, stakeholder mapping, and the mechanics of how laws move from draft to floor vote.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="program-phase">
        <span class="program-phase__number font-mono">03</span>
        <div class="program-phase__content">
          <h3 class="program-phase__name font-display">Mentor Pairing</h3>
          <p>Each fellow is paired with a senior policy professional, elected official, or legislative staffer who provides direct guidance throughout the fellowship.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="program-phase">
        <span class="program-phase__number font-mono">04</span>
        <div class="program-phase__content">
          <h3 class="program-phase__name font-display">Weekly Sessions</h3>
          <p>Cohort-wide working sessions where fellows present research, debate strategy, and sharpen their reform proposals against peers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="program-phase">
        <span class="program-phase__number font-mono">05</span>
        <div class="program-phase__content">
          <h3 class="program-phase__name font-display">Capstone Deliverable</h3>
          <p>Every fellow produces a capstone reform proposal&mdash;a publication-ready document targeting a specific issue in Texas law or local policy. This is not academic. It is built to be used.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

